               <msContents>
                  <summary>Declaration of camels; the first preserved lines tell of an order of the prefect that camel-owners furnish one fifth of their camels to the treasury</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; the back is blank</note>
                     <note type="general">22 lines of writing by two fast cursive hands</note>
                     <note type="general">The papyrus pushes the term of offfice of Flavius Hyginus back to the end of 330</note>
                     <note type="general">The otherwise unknown order of the prefect seems to refer to a  compulsory purchase; the very large numbers of camels involved would seem to presuppose an imperial campaign, perhaps of Constantius</note>
